Lee S. Simon M.D., FACP, FACR (USA): Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 25, 2017 6:03 PM ET
Healthcare Providers and Services

Company Overview of MEDACorp, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Lee S. Simon M.D., FACP, FACR (USA)Head Regulatory Consultant, MEDACorp, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 14 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Dr. Lee S. T. Simon, M.D., FACP, FACR (USA) has been the Head Regulatory Consultant at Leerink Swann/MEDACorp Consulting since March 2004 and MEDACorp, Inc. Dr. Simon serves as Nuclear Medicine Advisor at AAA Canada (a/k/a, Atreus Pharmaceuticals Corporation). Dr. Simon serves as a Principal at SDG LLC. He served at United States Food and Drug Administration and where he served as a Division Director of the Arthritis, Analgesic & Ophthalmologic Drug Product Division ... at the Center for Drug Evaluation and Research. He has also served as a consultant for DDMAC (1993), the American Hospital Formulary (1990) and AMA Drug Products (1990). He has over 25 years clinical experience at Harvard, Beth Israel Deaconess and Johns Hopkins University. Prior to his tenure at the FDA, Dr. Simon served as Director of Rheumatology Clinical Research and an Associate Chief of Medicine at Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center in Boston, MA. Dr. Simon served as Technical Advisor of Affinergy Inc. He serves as a Director of Cure Therapeutics, Inc. He has been a Member of Scientific Advisory Board at ImmuPharma Plc since July 2013. He serves as Member of Clinical Advisory Board at XTL Biopharmaceuticals Ltd. He serves as a Clinical Advisory Board Member for Viador-Calcitonin at TransPharma Medical Ltd. He serves as a Member of Scientific Advisory Board at MEDACorp., and Chelsea Therapeutics International Ltd. He has been a Member of Scientific Advisory Board of Nuvo Research Inc. (Formerly Dimethaid Research Inc.), since September 2005. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at PainReform Ltd. He served as a Director of Salem Regional Medical Center(also known as Salem Community Hospital). He served as a Director at Savient Pharmaceuticals, Inc. from May 2006 to December 28, 2012. He served as a Member of Advisory Board at Alder Biopharmaceuticals Inc until December 12, 2015. He served as a Member of the Scientific Advisory Board at Anthera Pharmaceuticals, Inc. since June 2010. Dr. Simon served as a Member of Scientific Advisory Board at Cadila Healthcare Limited. He served as member of scientific and development advisory board of Savient Pharmaceuticals, Inc since January 26, 2005. He is also an Associate Clinical Professor and the Co-course Director, Clinical Pharmacology HST of Medicine at Harvard Medical School. He is a leading rheumatologist from Harvard Medical School. He has been a Rheumatologist for 36 years. He has extensive experience in drug development in the US and has served on consulting advisory boards for many companies and federal associations including more than seven years as a voting member of various advisory committees tor the U.S. FDA, eventually serving as a Division Director of Analgesic, Anti- inflammatory and Ophthalmologic Drug Products for several years. He has served on editorial boards of multiple journals and has authored more than 110 original publications, review articles and chapters, as well as co-edited four books. He received the Distinguished Service Award from the American College of Rheumatology, the Scientific Leadership Award from the Lupus Research Institute and the SLE Foundation in 2003 and the Quality Performance Award and the Faculty Recognition Award from the FDA's Center for Drug Evaluation and Research. He is a fellow of the American College of Physicians (1991) and the American College of Rheumatology (1986). He has served for two terms on the Board of Directors of the American College of Rheumatology (ACR) (1991-1993, 1994-1997), served as the Chair of Education for the ACR and on the committee of the National Arthritis Foundation. He has served as the Scientific Abstract Selection Chair of the Annual Meeting of the ACR (2002). Dr. Simon attended Loyola College in Maryland. He received his Medical Degree from University of Maryland School of Medicine and trained in Internal Medicine at Johns Hopkins Hospital and in Rheumatology at the Massachusetts General Hospital.Read Full Background




