Executive Profile
Simon S. Lee  Founder and Chairman, STG Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 1 different industries.See Board Relationships68--
Background

		Mr. Simon S. Lee Founded STG Group, Inc. in 1986 and has been its Chairman of the Board since November 2015. Mr. Lee served as the Chief Executive Officer of STG Group, Inc. until November 2015 and served as its President until July 2012. Mr. Lee emigrated to the U.S. from South Korea in 1979. Beginning his career as an engineer, Mr. Lee performed in senior technical positions with various technology firms in the Washington area. Mr. Lee founded STG as Software Technology ... Group in 1986, to address the growing demand for high quality, Information Technology (IT) support services. His vision for STG Inc., came to realization in 1993 when the Department of State awarded STG its first large contract to develop the software for a global visa tracking system. Mr. Lee has led STG, Inc.'s evolution to a $170 million provider of performance-based IT, homeland security, engineering and scientific services with clients spanning across government and industry. He served as the Chairman of Global Defense & National Security Systems, Inc. since November 23, 2015 and served as its Director. Mr. Lee has received numerous awards in recognition of his services to industry and the community. In 2014, he was the first Korean-American to receive the George Washington University President’s Medal and was the recipient of a US Department of Commerce Lifetime Achievement Award in 2007 for his advancement of minority businesses. His Awards and Recognitions in December 2004 Korean Broadcasting Systems' Great Overseas Koreans Award, October 2004 Finalist for Executive of the Year, Greater Washington Contractor Awards, October 2003 Finalist for Executive of the Year, Greater Washington Contractor Awards, October 2003 Recipient of the Emerging Business Forum's American Dream Award, May 2003 Recipient of the Ellis Island Medal of Honor, June 2001 Recipient of the Pan-Asian American Excellence Award, 1998 and 1999 Finalist for the Ernst & Young “Entrepreneur of the Year” award. 1998 Recipient of the U.S. Small Business Administration's Small Business Person of the Year. Mr. Lee holds a Bachelor of Science in Industrial Engineering from Korea University and a Master of Science in Systems Engineering from the George Washington University.Read Full Background




